  "title": "Construction Site Manager",
  "description": "<p>A site manager's job description is to <strong>oversee and coordinate the daily operations of a construction site to ensure a project is completed on time, within budget, and according to safety regulations</strong>. Key responsibilities include managing staff and subcontractors, interpreting blueprints, conducting safety inspections, and handling administrative duties like budgets, reports, and permits.</p>\n<p>Core responsibilities</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Project management:</strong>Oversee the entire project from start to finish, managing timelines, resources, and budgets.</li>\n  <li><strong>Site supervision:</strong>Coordinate and supervise all on-site staff and subcontractors, including workers, electricians, and plumbers.</li>\n  <li><strong>Safety and compliance:</strong>Conduct regular safety inspections, enforce safety protocols, and ensure compliance with all relevant regulations and quality control procedures.</li>\n  <li><strong>Technical oversight:</strong>Interpret blueprints and technical drawings to ensure construction matches specifications and building codes.</li>\n  <li><strong>Administrative duties:</strong>Prepare site reports, manage paperwork, secure permits and licenses, and handle budgets.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Key skills</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Leadership:</strong> The ability to supervise, motivate, and coordinate teams.</li>\n  <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Strong communication skills to liaise effectively with clients, architects, surveyors, and other professionals.</li>\n  <li><strong>Problem-solving:</strong> Ability to proactively identify and solve problems that arise during the project.</li>\n  <li><strong>Technical knowledge:</strong> In-depth knowledge of the construction industry and construction management software.</li>\n  <li><strong>Time and budget management:</strong> Skills in managing budgets, timeframes, and resources efficiently.</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 10,
